{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "A study suggests that people aren\u2019t aware of the monthly variation in their cash flow and that many aren\u2019t prepared for a big spending month.", "abstract": "The Upshot: study undertaken by research group at JPMorgan Chase finds that some 41 percent of households experienced at least a 30 percent variation in monthly income between 2012 and 2014, and that 60 percent experienced a 30 percent variation in consumption; data indicates that Americans are not aware of monthly variation, and remain unprepared for low-income months.", "section_name": "The Upshot", "print_page": "3", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Binyamin", "role": "reported", "lastname": "APPELBAUM", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By BINYAMIN APPELBAUM"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/21/upshot/dont-assume-that-you-know-your-monthly-spending-and-income.html", "lead_paragraph": "A study suggests that people aren\u2019t aware of the monthly variation in their cash flow and that many aren\u2019t prepared for a big spending month.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Vague on Your Monthly Spending? You\u2019re Not Alone", "main": "Don\u2019t Assume That You Know Your Monthly Spending and Income", "content_kicker": "Everyday Economics", "kicker": "The Upshot"}, "_id": "555ce53f38f0d846c796f107", "word_count": "781", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/05/21/upshot/21up-spend/21up-spend-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/05/21/upshot/21up-spend/21up-spend-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2015/05/21/upshot/21up-spend/21up-spend-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/05/21/upshot/21up-spend/21up-spend-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/05/21/upsh